id: pm-0hnu
title: Structured remediation map on pm health --json for all non-extension checks
description: "Agents consuming pm health --json get warning codes (history_drift_missing_stream, integrity_item_unreadable, telemetry_queue_pending, vectorization_stale) but must hardcode the fix; only extensions return triage.remediation."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[5]: agent-ux,"area:health","area:observability",living-map,telemetry
created_at: "2026-05-31T19:45:02.363Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-04T22:17:44.191Z"
author: maintainer-agent
acceptance_criteria: "Each check detail gains remediation_map (warning-code-prefix -> fix command) e.g. history_drift->pm history-repair <id>, vectorization->pm health --refresh-vectors; brief omits it; full includes it; test asserts a non-empty map."
value: "Agents consuming pm health --json get warning codes (history_drift_missing_stream, integrity_item_unreadable, telemetry_queue_pending, vectorization_stale) but must hardcode the fix; only extensions return triage.remediation."
parent: pm-5oj5
resolution: Added details.remediation_map (warning-code-prefix -> executable pm fix command) to every non-extension health check via the shared registry src/core/diagnostics/remediation.ts; brief/summary omit it; extensions keep details.triage.remediation.
expected_result: Agents read a fix command per warning code from pm health --json without hardcoding mappings.
actual_result: history_drift/vectorization/integrity/settings/telemetry/directories checks now carry remediation_map when they warn; verified in sandbox.
